countryOverview:
Sierra Leone, officially the Republic of Sierra Leone, is a country in West Africa. It is bordered by Guinea to the north and east, Liberia to the south-east, and the Atlantic Ocean to the west and south-west. Sierra Leone has a population of around 5.4 million. Freetown is the capital, largest city and economic and financial centre. The other major cities are Bo, Kenema, Koidu Town and Makeni.
<br><br>Sierra Leone is now a constitutional republic with a directly elected president and a unicameral legislature, known as the House of Parliament. The president is the head of state and the Head of government. The Judiciary of Sierra Leone is independent of the executive and the legislature, but its judges are appointed by the president.
<br><br>Sierra Leone is divided into four geographical regions: the Northern Province,Eastern Province,Southern Province and the Western Area; which are further divided into fourteen districts. Each district has its own directly elected local government called district council, headed by a Council Chairman. The country's six municipalities of Freetown, Bo, Kenema, Koidu Town, Makeni and Bonthe in turn have directly elected city councils, headed by mayors.<br><br>The country is rich in diamonds and other minerals. The trade in illicit gems, are known as 'blood diamonds' for their role in funding conflicts, which perpetuated the civil war.&nbsp;<br><br>Sierra Leone is recovering from a 10-year civil war which ended in 2002. In terms of its economy, it has grown substantially in recent years, however, it still remains bottom of the UN's league for human development.&nbsp;

